{"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/GWeakCapturing","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TypeModuleRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The model of ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTypeModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a dynamically loaded module which","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implements some number of types and interface implementations.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the module is loaded, it registers its types and interfaces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using [method"},{"code":"GObject.TypeModule.register_type","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.add_interface"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"As long as any instances of these types and interface implementations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are in use, the module is kept loaded. When the types and interfaces","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are gone, the module may be unloaded. If the types and interfaces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"become used again, the module will be reloaded. Note that the last"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference cannot be released from within the module code, since that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"would lead to the caller’s code being unloaded before ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns to it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Keeping track of whether the module should be loaded or not is done by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using a use count - it starts at zero, and whenever it is greater than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"zero, the module is loaded. The use count is maintained internally by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type system, but also can be explicitly controlled by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypeModule.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.unuse"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Typically, when loading a module for the first type, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_type_module_use()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will be used to load it so that it can initialize its types. At some later"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"point, when the module no longer needs to be loaded except for the type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"implementations it contains, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_type_module_unuse()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"GTypeModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does not actually provide any implementation of module"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"loading and unloading. To create a particular module type you must","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"derive from "},{"code":"GTypeModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and implement the load and unload functions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"GTypeModuleClass","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GTypeModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypeModuleRef"}],"symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","title":"TypeModuleRef","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibOb